        <num>CC 2036</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 12.  REVOCATORY ACTION AND OBLIQUE ACTION
SECTION 1.  REVOCATORY ACTION
Art. 2036.  Act of the obligor that causes or increases his insolvency
An obligee has a right to annul an act of the obligor, or the result of a failure to act of the obligor, made or effected after the right of the obligee arose, that causes or increases the obligor's insolvency.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109295</p>
        </authorialNote>
